here's a php version <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" /><br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&lt;?php<br /><br />$wav = file_get_contents&#40;'wavefile.raw'&#41;;<br />$len = strlen&#40;$wav&#41;;<br />$newwav = '';<br /><br />for &#40;$i = 0; $i &lt; $len; $i++&#41;<br />&#123;   $newwav .= chr&#40; ord&#40;substr&#40;$wav,$i,1&#41;&#41; &gt;&gt; 1 &#41;;<br />&#125;<br /><br />file_put_contents&#40;'newwave.raw', $newwav&#41;;<br /><br />?&gt;</div><br /><br />or change the code to use .wav files with a standard header<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">$newwav = substr&#40;$wav, 0, 0x2C&#41;;<br /><br />for &#40;$i = 0x2C; $i &lt; $len; $i++&#41;</div><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3841">frantik</a> — Tue Mar 31, 2009 4:32 pm</p><hr />
